hits.text: I proudly announce the winner of my #bestveggieburgerofamsterdam competition! My absolute favorite vegetarian burger in Amsterdam is (drumroll please).... the Dutch Weed Burger! 🏆  There are so many reasons to like it that I don't know where to start. The patty is one of the few ones that I tried that didn't fell apart. The bun is rich in taste and crispy. The Dutch Weed Burger is fully plant based, so suitable for vegans and great news for our planet. It's also kosher, halal and quite healthy as it contains seaweed and chlorella. And one of the best things about it? It's available at many places throughout the Netherlands, and sometimes even abroad (it'll be in London on October 22nd). I hope that my list inspires you and I'd love to hear your thoughts if you tried one of the veggie burgers on my list!

Heard a story of someone riding over a bridge on the Prinsengracht recently. They did that thing when a tourist potters right in the middle of the road and the rider dings their bell loudly at the last minute and zooms past. Kind of like Tom Cruise in Top Gun flying by unsuspecting air control towers. Well, in this instance, the tourist got so spooked that they leaped out of the way and proceeded to trip over another tourist’s rolling suitcase on their way to the ground. We’ve reached capacity people. Welcome to another edition of “Amsterdam in July: The Hordes Are Upon Us.” We added a Collection of events, openings, and things to do in July to Sightseen. You can find it on the homepage in the app or as a post on the Sightseen Medium account. Check it out and message us if we missed anything. 🎶 Take me on a Magic carpet ride..... 🎶 Today's box was a culinary journey inspired by a recent trip to Morocco & the desert 🌴  A quarter aubergine, slow roasted 'til nice and crispy, then painted with a fresh garlic, lemon & tahini sauce, garnished with chopped mint & sesame seeds | chickpeas marinated with a blend of Moroccan spices, cinnamon heavy, with thinly sliced raw red onion | brown rice laced with parsley, citrus, dill, fresh orange segments, black olives & toasted almonds | A whole roasted & peeled Romano pepper curled up with cashew, date, lemon verbena & basil pesto | pickled red onion & perfectly cubed carrot & butternut salad with chilli & wild cumin dressing | spicy mung bean pate with lots of lemon & the holy trinity -chilli, garlic & ginger.... All garnished with pomegtanate rubies & rose petals... Pheeew that's a tummy full o' happiness 😉  How did you enjoy your #Cropbox today? They are as big as a 12 inch pizza and when topped with toppings like bacon, chicken, et al, the world just becomes much better to live in. Top this off with a generous helping of dutch maple syrup and you have a winning combo. And De Vier Pilaren does one of the best pancakes and poffertjes around! Highly recommended.  #bacon #pancakes #amsterdamfood Follow for more delicious food pics. Heute Morgen waren wir (wie jeden Morgen) im Bagels&Beans frühstücken. Es ist eine Amsterdamer Café-Kette, die sehr stark auf Nachhaltigkeit und Natürlichkeit setzt. Alles wird super frisch zubereitet und schmeckt wahnsinnig lecker. Man kann aus acht verschiedenen Bagels wählen - es gibt sogar einen weizen- und einen glutenfreien. Zum Frühstück gab es heuten den Oathie-Bagel mit Hummus, Hühnchen, Salat und Mango-Chutney 😋 Jetzt sind wir mit fast einer Stunde Verspätung auf dem Weg gen Heimat. Happy Weekend! The Dutch have handed down the chairmanship of the EU to the Slovakians, which means that the former Marine Land of the Dutch Navy is ours again! Reason for us to explore this extraordinary piece of land adjacent to the Scheepvaartmuseum with its replica of the VOC tall ship 'Amsterdam' at which a beautiful view is granted. The terrace is one of its most pleasant surprises. As is the beer menu. From fresh to the more dark beers, all with a special twist. The combination makes for a great evening on the waterside. That was our first evening. We went back for lunch in the bar. And that was good too. Service was friendly though sometimes a little slow. The sandwiches are tasty and the juices refreshing. And they know how to make a good espresso. Drop by when you are in the hood! We continued to the Scheepskameel. Dutch bitterballen at @foodhallen in Amsterdam last week. These were a selection of beef, chorizo and goats cheese, but there was also truffle and bouillabaisse. Very addictive and perfect with a few beers.

Amsterdam special #5 : Bitterballen (Dutch meatballs). What can I say about these heavenly delicious meatballs apart from that they will make you go YUM! The perfect accompaniment to a tall glass of chilled beer (or even just alone), these little balls of flavor are filled with beef, broth, flour, and herbs for flavor before they are deep-fried. Be careful when you bite into them; the liquid filling can be super hot. Definitely recommended!  Follow for more delicious food pics. This is Back to Black (@backtoblackcoffee), a great little cafe near the Rijksmuseum.  Whereas in most cities the terms are interchangeable, in Amsterdam, there's definitely a distinction between a “coffee shop” & a “cafe.” The importance of this distinction depends entirely on your mood, sense of adventure, & probationary status.  All Amsterdamers have stories of visitors naively announcing - “Where are these weed shops? Let's toke some green!” Nobody sounds cool saying “toke some green,” & it’s in these situations when Amsterdamers are forced to flip the big kill-switch known as “Project De-escalation: Keep Uncle Steve Away From The Weed.” Step 1 involves a long bike ride followed by trips to brewery/tasting rooms like Borouwer'ij (@brouwerijtij) or Butcher's Tears. If you can sneak in a few rounds of bitterballen with the heavy beers, it’s likely your charge will forget their boastful weed promises.  If Step 1 doesn’t work, Step 2 suggests a visit to a mellow coffee shop & slyly ordering - “Mag ik je zwakste weed? I have an idiot tourist who doesn't need anything stronger than hash cut with a ton of rolling tobacco.” Once in hand, take your visitor on a walk to smoke & see the city. They’ll last 30-45 minutes before crashing back at the hotel/AirBnb/your extra bedroom. Easy peasy!  The worst situation is when the visitor stays energetic through the bike ride, dubbels, bitterballen, & your kind offer to order weed. If they say “It's cool, dude. I’ve smoked a lot of weed, I know the score,” the only option is traditional Dutch directness. “No, Uncle Steve, you don't know the score. In fact, the score has been hydroponically mutated to such levels that you're going to end up wobbling down Leidsestraat wearing a knit Amsterdam beanie and asking strangers for the ‘Hanses Blinkers Hotel.’ I don't want to be on a cold bench listening to you repeatedly slur 'I might puke,' while my actual friends have normal evenings. But, hey, you get to go back to Rochester or Atlanta or Fort Worth & tell everyone about the time you were ‘in Amsterdam looking for coffee and ended up at a coffee shop.’” Find the best coffee & coziest cafes in Amsterdam on Sightseen.

// Pancakes Amsterdam 🥞 // 🗺 Prinsengracht 277, 1016 GW Amsterdam, Pays-Bas ✍🏻 Coralie 3/5 // Moi : 3,5/5 🇫🇷 Avec @coralie_jeanne nous avons passé 3 jours à Amsterdam pour son anniversaire, voici donc un petit interlude néerlandais avec des pancakes 😋 Coralie : C'était bon mais pas surprenant. Les serveuses étaient adorables mais le lieu grand et blanc fait assez aseptisé, ça détonne un peu pour moi, je mets un 3/5. Moi : Le pancake néerlandais ressemble en fait à une grosse crêpe, ou une "pescajoun" de mon enfance, spécialité du quercy, c'était bon, parfait pour le petit déjeuner et le service était vraiment très agréable, les gens à amsterdam sont des anges ! Je mets un bémol sur le fait que leurs toilettes soient payants 50c, un restaurant, pour moi, se doit d'offrir l'accès à des sanitaires gratuitement ! Nous avons pris le pancake salé le plus cher et à 12,5€ cela reste très correct. 🇬🇧 Coralie : Waitresses are very nice but the place is big and white, not very warm. The food is good but not amazing.  Moi : Netherlands pancakes look like the "pescajoun", a thick crepe from my county, memory of my childhood, it was good. One bad point for the place is that you have to pay 50c to go to the toilet and I think every restaurant should let you access the toilet for free. We took the most expensive pancake and it was 12,5€ so quite correct.  #pancakes

"Geef mij maar Amsterdam, dat is mooier dan Parijs" - Johnny Jordaan  The Jordaan - traditional home of the dramatic vibrato that is Jordaanlied music and current home of Amsterdam's “most beautiful canal," De Brouwersgracht. A wobbly grid of quiet, narrow streets, the Jordaan is as much Amsterdam heritage as wooden shoes & rain.  On Rozengracht, along the bottom edge of the Jordaan, you'll find Salmuera (@sal_amsterdam) w/ an exceptional mix of cocktails & ceviche. Further down, the terrace at Brandstof (@barbrandstof) is the perfect place to observe one of the great spectacles of Amsterdam – the convergence of pedestrian, bike, scooter, car, taxi, bus, & tram. Who will win?? (SPOILER – It's usually the tram.) Heading north off Rozengracht leads into the Jordaan & over some of the city's prettiest canals. If you get nice light & want to win Instagram, Egelantiersgracht (#egelantiersgracht) & Bloemgracht (#bloemgracht) are great options.  Saturday mornings on Westerstraat, you can either have beers & cigarettes with the locals at De Blaffende Vis (#blaffendevis) or head to the organic market at the Noorderkerk (#noorderkerkmarket). If looking for dinner, De Reiger (#dereiger) has maybe the best ribs in Amsterdam & definitely the coolest restaurant cat. Daalder (#daalder), in a former jazz bar on Lindengracht, also has great food, but unconfirmed if there’s a restaurant cat.  After dinner (or anytime really), the Jordaan has a solid supply of brown bars. Cafe Thijsen (@cafe_thijssen) & De Tuin (#cafedetuin) are usually fun. But if you're looking for a truly “cultural” experience, the fluorescent pink, late-night beacon of Cafe Nol (@cafenolamsterdam) will definitely blow up anything you have to do the next morning.  For more Jordaan suggestions, check out the Sightseen app.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. The Breakfast Club has opened a new branch on the Haarlemmerplein, which is still underdeveloped in terms of bars, restaurants and especially terraces. Where the first Breakfast Club is known for serving breakfast all day, here you can also enjoy dinner. Breakfast and lunch during the weekend are packed here. We went for a salad of the new dinner menu and it was very quiet. Portion wise we were not fully satisfied, but the price and taste was right. We got a nice salad with cray fish, loads of those little guys actually. It could have had a serving of bread and a little more green salad. And a price adjustment from now 10 to let's say 12 euros would be fine for dinner! Service was ok. Friendly, helpful, but they were struggling a little bit with the new menu. We will come back for another salad or the famous breakfast pancakes. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #breakfast #lunch # dinner #drinks #cocktails #restaurant #thebreakfastclub #thebreakfastclub.nl #haarlemmerplein #westerpark #amsterdamwest #salad #crayfish #pancakes #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

This amazing barber shop located between Dam square and Central station is not only a great place for you gentlemans to go for a good cut or trim but now also serves a delicious New Zealand style brunch and an American inspired diner 7 days a week next door. If cheese is your mistress, then @kaashuistromp is your Holiday Inn. Explore the lekker world of Dutch cheese right here (numerous locations, pictured here, our favourite by the 9 streets, on Elandsgracht in the Jordaan). Holland is best known for its hard/semi-hard cheeses (Gouda, Edam, etc) but the selection at Tromp is broad, staff are knowledgeable, and the samples are generous!! Located in the magnificent De Hallen cultural complex in Amsterdam’s hip Oud-West neighbourhood, Foodhallen is a classy indoor food market and bar serving up a range of high-end street food and beverages in historic surroundings. There are around 20 street food vendors serving up everything from wood-fired pizzas to Vietnamese summer rolls and Greek meze to artisanal burgers from some of Amsterdam’s best-loved kitchens.

Wat weet jij over pistache (ijs)? De pistache noten uit ons ijs komen uit Bronte, dat ligt aan de voet van de Etna in Sicilië. Sicilië is de enige plek op aarde waar pistachenoten worden geteeld. De oogst is één keer in de twee jaar, zodat de boom haar kracht kan behouden. De minerale zouten in de vulkanische aarde zorgen voor een unieke zilte nasmaak. De smaak van ijs laat zich niet anders beschrijven dan echt pistache! #vansoest #utrechtsestraat #chocolade #chocolate #iamsterdam #amsterdamcityguide #lostinamsterdam #amsterdamworld #amsterdamcity #amsterdamtrip #amsterdamshots #amsterdamfood #amsterdamlife #atamsterdam #pistache #pistacheijs #icecream #icecreamamsterdam

De School is wonderful initiative in a former technical school in Amsterdam-West, including a club, music venue, restaurant, cafe, gym and an exhibition space. Some of the former classrooms are now the domain of local creative companies. I’ve recently visited the Restaurant DS, located in the open workshop. It is a bit hard to find, but if you’ve managed to get here, you will enjoy this raw venue that provides a nice balance between the initial industrial function of the space and the restaurant’s linen and candlelight. It was a pleasant surprise that vegetables play a central role in all their menus! (Photo ©: De School)

AMSTERDAM • There are macaroons, and then there are kokosmakronen - coconut macaroons! We tried some amazing ones found at Noodermarkt.  From @thedutchtable: Dutch have an incredible cookie culture. Grocery stores stock shelves of the most amazing combinations, shapes, ingredients and flavors. Coconut macaroons, or kokosmakronen, are found in a variety of shapes and sizes. Some are small and high, others piped in a circle and flat. Some are yellow (depending on whether you include the egg yolk), others plain white, but the flavor and texture is always moist, coconutty and sweet. Kokosmakronen are usually baked on circles of edible potato starch paper.

The 'Dam might be known for its 'coffee shops', but the actual coffee scene is pretty damn good if you know where to look (pun intended). Back to Black was one of a few great recs from a colleague/fellow coffee snob, and besides the awesome artisan coffee the apple pie we had was next level.

The neighbourfood cafe Bar Mick is in the middle of the upcoming Spaarndammerstraat. It opens at 9 for coffee and breakfast and serves different menus throughout the day. The dinner menu only has meat and vegetarian options. We ordered the bavette and veggie burger, but the waiter mentioned that the vegetarian burger was actually not that good and advised us the vegetarian ravioli. So we did.  The bavette was cut with the grain, so not as tender as this 20,50 € costing larded piece of meat should be. The ravioli was well undercooked. Add up the waiter that folds up the laundry in the bar during service, literally reads up the daily specials from the chalk board behind us and we come to the conclusion that there are far better ways to spend your euros. We go for better! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️ Service ⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #bar #cafe #restaurant #barmick #barmick.nl #spaarndammerstraat #westerpark #spaarndammerbuurt #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

Loetje Centraal has touched down last year in the wooden coffee house opposite of Amsterdam Central Station.  It all started long ago in the Pijp with the small and cosy Cafe Loetje. Their secret is a commonly known fact by now: They bake the very tender meat in plain Blue Band. The "Loetje Group" now has 9 restaurants including their latest addition in Gorssel of all places. The Little Princess became a Disneyland. But what do we learn from Disneyland? They offer quality, staff is well trained and the ambiance fine. And we all love a bit of  that sometimes. But still it feels like "Honey, they blew up Cafe Loetje". ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #lunch # diner #restaurant #loetje #loetje.com #centralstation #stationsplein #depijp #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

To cool off from the jalapenno🌶I made The zucchini mango salad🙏🏻. ———————————————— INGREDIENTS: 1 zucchini  1 mango  10 cherry tomatoes  2 tbsp rice vinegar 1 tbsp roasted sesame seed A pinch of pepper A pinch of salt. ———————————————— INSTRUCTIONS 1. Make the zucchine small in the spiralizer.  2. Cut the mango in small slices.  3. Roast the sesame seed in a pan.  4. Cut the cherry tomatoes in four.  5. Blend everything with the rice vinegar in a bowl and at some pepper and salt. Enjoy!  #amsterdamfood #amsterdam #veganamsterdam #food #salad #mangosalad #spiralizer #healthyfood #friendscooking #photooftheday

Cantinetta is owned by the Dutch/American couple Claudia and Deborah. The latter is showing off her cooking talent and Italian roots in the kitchen, while Claudia is serving the dishes in the Roman inspired osteria. They prepare their own pastas during the day, which make up the most of the menu. The wine list changes very frequently as well as part of the menu. Fortunately the side dish of the non pasta main stays the same: mashed potato (with pancetta! 😋) and endive. AMSTERDAM • A date with @annabelgreeve at Amsterdam's most famous park - Vondel Park. Top plate is the 'Amsterdam' platter with pate, tartare, cheese. The other plate is bitterballen - a typical meat based Dutch snack with a mixture of beef or veal, flour. A bit like a croquette.

We love La Stage. It has become one of our favorite intimate restaurants in Amsterdam. Great to impress a date with mouth watering dishes, perfect service and even greater wine and food pairings. This restaurant close to the Nieuwmarkt has applied their proof of a Michelin star in the kitchen and doesn't show it off on their front window. It is exemplary for the modesty of the two partnered owners. In working life they divided the jobs clearly: he is in white, she is in black. The whites surprise you with creative and beautiful balanced dishes served in 4- to 6-course a la carte menus, the blacks indulge you with wonderful wines served with passion and knowledge. An empty table is rare, so reservations are advised. All in all a great place to celebrate life! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #dinner #restaurant #lastage #restaurantlastage.nl #geldersekade #nieuwmarkt #amsterdamcentrum #mackerel #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram #theartofplating

First a short history lesson: Escoffier is seen as the greatest innovator of French cuisine and having learned everything from him, Henri Thijs returned to the Netherlands to open a deli-restaurant combination together with entrepreneur Dikker. This combination was new to the Netherlands and was an instant hit. The succes story is larded with multiple branches, prices, a Michelin star, and the opening of an hotel. Back to here and now. We passed by for lunch and had two of the classic salads. The Niçoise salad came with a severe piece of freshly grilled tuna and other fine ingredients including a poached (we love it poached) egg. The tuna had some natural tough membrane, which made us fillet the fillet. But hey, that happens. We found ingredients of the same quality in our Caesar salad with chicken. Classic and perfectly served. Bread came after we asked for some pieces. The restaurant is styled in a modern and warm way, leaving room for the old brick wall and other original details. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— Thijs by Dikker & Thijs Prinsengracht 438 (near Leidsestraat) 020-6250150, reservations possible www.thijsbydikkerenthijs.nl Open: Sun-Thu 10.00-0.00, Fri-Sat 10.00-1.00 ——— #coffee #lunch #dinner #drinks #prinsengracht #leidsestraat #escoffier #hautecuisine #amsterdamcentre #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

Ahhh...a sunny Sunday in Amsterdam. Does it get any better? Boats on the canals, packed terraces, biking through the park. Lekker weertje!  On the way to @boccacoffee today, we passed a wobbly tourist completely off his tits with chunks of vomit dripping from his beard. Not bad for noon on a Sunday. (“Goed zo, meneer! Enjoy your flight back to Luton!”) A few minutes later, we were delivered this display of civility pictured above. The card you can't read because of the overwhelming amount of filters applied to this poorly shot image describes the tea at hand. Apparently, it's “blossomed, dewy, and bouquet.” If you've ever walked into @boccacoffee and wondered - “How is it possible for this huge, beautiful space to exist in the Centrum? I mean, there's only like 12 seats. How do they make any money?”, it's because @boccacoffee is an anomaly that should be celebrated. Rumor has it that the shop on Kerkstraat is a flagship and not-so-top-secret training facility for Bocca Coffee operatives. Basically, we get to enjoy spacious, high-ceilinged, “blossomed, dewy, and bouquet” Sundays while Bocca takes a hit on the lavish space in the name of bettering the brand overall. Fair trade!* (*Bad coffee joke.) Check out @boccacoffee and find all the best coffee places in Amsterdam for your sunny Sundays with the Sightseen App.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. Another follow up to my last two posts 😬  After eating all that food me and my family then went and chilled in a coffee shop all day drinking lattes and smoking - come the evening me and my dad had the munchies big time lol! We hadn't been to no waffle houses so far so on the way back we stopped in the #1 rated Waffle House @metropolitandeli and got waffles, cakes and ice cream haha  Didn't get a good picture of the waffles but they were smothered in white chocolate sauce I got 2 servings of red velvet cake with salted caramel ice cream and my dad got 2 servings of bread and butter pudding cake 😂 - was honestly unreal and the perfect way to finish such a sick new years holiday  The eating didn't stop there though, at the airport I ended up getting a maestro burger meal too which funny enough was the best mcdonalds I've ever had looooool  Amsterdam is possibly the best place to go after 20 weeks of dieting if you ain't worried about getting fatter than you have ever been before  Was a bit gutted I put on pounds upon pounds but if I could go back I would do it all again 👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻 #Amsterdam #amsterdamcity #amsterdamfood #amsterdamlife #food #foodporn #redvelvet #redvelvetcake  #breadandbuttercake #saltedcaramel #saltedcaramelicecream #waffles #dessert #travel #travelfood #tripadvisor #toprated #iifym #flexibledieting #reversediet #10000calories #bodybuilding #fitness #physique #newyears #instafood

There's a burger under that egg! Amsterdam had THE BEST food and I'm a picky eater (getting better). I was walking to another place and passed this restaurant on my way and came back another day. I was sick coming from Iceland and had a wicked sore throat my first couple of days in Amsterdam. I got this delicious and huge burger with equally delicious and fresh fries. Every thing was seasoned and so so good. They had a tea which soothed my throat almost instantaneously as well with lemon ginger and honey. I left stuffed and took home a slice of chocolate pie which was also amazing. The decor of this place was super cute and service was great. Recommend 10/10 Betty Blue for anyone passing through Amsterdam.  #bettyblue #food #foodporn #foodie #eaaats #eeeeeats #instafood #amsterdamfood #burgers #eggs #sunnysideegg #fries #amsterdamlife #travel #holland #netherlands #amsterdam #tea #nederlands

🇫🇷Vous venez bientôt visiter Amsterdam? Voici le bon plan pour découvrir Amsterdam en vélo: @amsterdamvelo 🚲.Vous pouvez planifier un tour avec un des guides, ils sont tous Français et au top! Ou bien, juste pour louer des vélos ! J'ai eu la chance de faire un tour et j'ai adoré: nous visitons le VRAI Amsterdam. Leurs vélos sont très discrets. Vous pouvez presque prétendre être un vrai Néerlandais 😝 🇬🇧Planning on visiting Amsterdam soon? Here is the good plan to explore the city on a bike: @amsterdamvelo 🚲. You can plan a tour with a guide (with a sexy French accent as they are French 😜). You can also just rent a bike there! I was lucky enough to try the tour and I loved it: you will explore the REAL Amsterdam. The bicycles are nice, cheap and discreet, you can cycle around pretending you are one of them 😝

Amsterdam'ın en güzel sokak lezzeti duraklarından biri de kuşkusuz ki çiğ ringa balığı ağırlıklı olmak üzere çiğ balık satan "haring" ciler. @winkel43 e giderken tam Singel'in başlangıç noktasında yer alan "Stubbe's Haring" beni gerçekten memnun etti. Küp küp doğranmış soğan ve turşu ile sunulan balık tam da benim damak zevkime göre. Suşi sevenler ekstra hoşlanacaktır. Hoog tijd voor een nieuwe post!! Als je nog niet weet waar je het zoeken moet vandaag, sta dan nu op om boodschappen te gaan doen bij de leukste toko van Amsterdam-Oost. En ja, ook als je in Fijnaart woont. Link in bio! "Boodschappen doen vind ik doorgaans leuk en fijn. Ik heb het dan niet over even snel een doos eieren halen, een flesje kookroom en een pak crackers omdat het echt niet anders kan maar ik heb het over die momenten dat je ruim de tijd neemt om je voorraadkastjes bij te vullen met ludieke producten die je lievelings zijn of die je nooit eerder at. Als ik weken beleef waarin ik veel (onder)weg ben en weinig thuis, dan is een partijtje goed boodschappen doen de perfecte remedie tegen die ontheemdheid. Ik woon in een fantastische buurt wat dat betreft. Ik denk zelfs dat die buurt in de top 3 van leukste boodschappenbuurten van Nederland valt. Wow! Maak ik even een statement." #toko #amsterdamoost #amsterdamfood #dappermarkt #dapperbuurt #surinaams #saoto #sopropo #sult #parbo

📒🖋 Op zaterdag 4 maart zal er in Creative Haus een schrijfcursus worden georganiseerd door Nelleke Lamme-den Boer!  Voor meer informatie  verwijzen we jullie door naar onze Facebook pagina!  Maar hier alvast  wat meer informatie over Nelleke zelf:  Nelleke Lamme-den Boer is docent Creatief schrijven. Vanuit haar bedrijf Tekstkwartier organiseert zij cursussen en workshop in en buiten Amsterdam. Zij schrijft poëzie en korte verhalen. Ze is een ongebundelde dichter en treedt regelmatig op om haar werk te kunnen voordragen. Schrijven is voor haar een manier van vormgeven, een rustgevend creatief proces.  Zien we jullie op 4 maart? Ormai è un rito andare a trovare l'amico @sandervanmelick ... la ricchezza dei suoi piatti riesce a spingermi sempre sino ai campi... al mare... alle stalle... assapori la freschezza... e la sua territorialità.  Amo la sua concentrazione mentre pensa a te, invitato della serata. Pensa a come amerai sorprenderti masticando lentamente sapori profumi... nei piatti di Sander trovi l'Olanda un  Olanda reale. Ma anche la capacita di incastonate la croccantezza  di altri paesi come l'Italia con il suo letto di cavolo nero a sua maestà il cervo... grazie, un grazie dal profondo del cuore amico Sander... P.S. La chicca della serata è stata la mis en bouche, un crostino con caviale di aringa... #cafemodern_amsterdam  #sandervanmelick #amsterdam #amsterdamfood #amsterdamnoord #amsterdamcity #amsterdamworld #amsterdamcity #amsterdamcityguide #we_heart_amsterdam #wanderful_holland #iamsterdam #unlimitedamsterdam #visitamsterdam #amsterdamsfinest #amsterdamvibes #amsterdamshots #amsterdamlove #unnapoletanoaparigi #mangiarecomeunavolta

"Twaalf jaar geleden kwam onze droom uit om in het hartje van Amsterdam mensen kennis te laten maken met onze eigen recepten en eten. We verbouwen zelf al vele jaren onze eigen groentes en kunnen je zodoende precies vertellen wat er op je bord ligt. Er worden geen bestrijdingsmiddelen en andere onvriendelijke methodes gebruikt om jou van een heerlijke lunch of high tea te voorzien, alles is puur en eerlijk! Op veler verzoek hebben we onze recepten samen gebundeld en kun je nu ook ons kookboek kopen. Wel op tijd bij zijn, want dat loopt harder dan we ooit hadden durven hopen...!" #amsterdam #denhaag #rotterdam #utrecht #leiden ##haarlem #nijmegen #leeuwarden #groningen #hightea #recepten #lunch #interview #amstelveen #zoetermeer #theetijd #biologisch #eerlijketen #organicfood #mooiemensen #amsterdamcity #amsterdamfood #amsterdamhotspot

We have a Fish and Chips revival in Amsterdam. Viscafé De Gouden Hoek, close to the Westerpark, was the first offering mainly Fish and Chips from daily catches. We love the ambiance which is very stylish and strengthening the concept. Here is what they do menu wise: some classic startes like croquettes, oysters and crab, but the main focus is of course on fish and chips. You choose one of the daily catches and combine it with one of three crusts with accompanying sauce. Choose from the classic crust with remoulade, a panko-crust with piccalilli or tempura-crust with Japanese Sriracha. When you don’t have enough at hand, daily catches ask for good communication between kitchen and service staff. Which in our case didn't go very well. We were surprised when two out of three dishes served had a totally different fish then the one we had ordered. And we had to find out ourselves. Ah what the heck, the taste was good. Service wasn’t to stable though. Some get it, others don’t. Do we recommend this place? Yup! We like the concept, we love the taste, maybe they can improve service a little. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— Viscafé De Gouden Hoek Van Limburg Stirumstraat 10A  020-2299009, reservations advised www.degoudenhoek.nl  Open: Tue-Fri 17.00-0.00, Sat-Sun 16.00-0.00 ——— #dinner #fishandchips #westerpark #staatsliedenbuurt #amsterdamwest #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

Fondant au chocolat! By traditional french recipe. It has a nice crunchy texture on the outside. But it is so soft and silky smooth in the center. I always make sure not to cook it too much so the center stays a bit gooey and moist. Yummmm!!!!

The fondue at Café Bern is typically shared by 2 – 4 people, so they serve a big basket of bread (about 2 full baguettes, divided into 4 pieces, and pre-cut for smaller bites). - I had the weirdest encounter!  I was dining at the bar and a couple was next to me with my bread basket sort of between this woman and me.  We had exchanged a few words, pleasantries, then I began to eat. Next thing she says to me (as she is taking some of MY bread), “I’m going to eat some of your food.” I don’t know that I said anything, but my face said more than enough because she immediately apologized and wouldn’t stop apologizing.  Incredibly presumptuous and weird! 😱 😜Not that I couldn’t share, but it was so shocking that she would just help herself and announce, not ask if she could. They were getting their own food, so not sure what that was about, but I was in Amsterdam, so maybe she had smoked a lil too much herb 😂😂 Here’s the lovely fondue I ate. #ChowChick 🍞🍞🧀🍞🧀🍞🧀🍞🍞

A major highlight of our whole trip so far...stumbling across a fantastic international food festival on our first night in Amsterdam. Hands down best outdoor street festival I've ever experienced...incredible selection of gourmet street food, amazingly original stalls/food trucks, awesome multiple venue live music and the best people watching ever. We love Amsterdam already:) #foodfestival #rollendekeukens #amsterdamlife #amsterdamfood #europetravel #foodtrucks #streetfood

When I was away on my trip I always made it a habit to have food at cafes and not inside overwhelming fancy restaurants. Reason being that restaurants that serve all kinds of cuisines generally never have quality food 🙄 (unless you are dining at a really really costly one). Cafes on the other hand never disappoint and fit ones budget. Italian cafes serve awesome italian food, spanish cafes serve awesome spanish food and so on. 🤘  I fell in love with pizzas all over again 😄 Don't want to sound harsh but I really don't like the kind of pizzas chains like Dominos and Pizza Hut sell here.  Italian cafes on the other hand served awesome italian food all round let alone pizzas. I fell in love with Tuna fish toppings 😁 I miss the food I had all through the trip 😞  Nice memories! 😊  #streetsofamsterdam #amsterdam #amsterdamfood #italiancafe #pizzalovers #pizzaislovepizzaislife #europe #eurotrip2015

I never throw food away and I love initiatives that want to reduce food waste!  So I'm a big fan of Instock, this #Amsterdam restaurant serves a 3 course meal made with food that supermarkets would have thrown away otherwise. And the dishes taste just as good as any other restaurant! Look at these cauliflower-corn patties with mixed vegetables for example! 🙌 Ps: they're opening up a 2nd restaurant in #thehague soon! #instocknl

Hoofdstad Brasserie is situated on the waterside of Hotel de L’Europe. It is a beautiful spot overlooking the canals and the Munt Tower. The food is classic and okay, but taking the price into consideration, offers little surprises. Let’s say it is on the safe side. The restaurant has been highlighted by Michelin with a bib gourmand, which stands for 'exceptional good food for moderate prices'. Well, we don’t agree on any of both statements. The hotel was renovated recently but the brasserie still gives you a little bit of an outdated feeling. The terrace furniture is severely affected by the Dutch weather and is ready to be replaced. Service wise: dishes were placed at the wrong guests and service itself isn’t as adequate as you would expect at a 5 star hotel. Come on! It should be possible to do better on such a beautiful location. Maybe it is a good spot for pensionados to spent their money and we are just not the type of guest they want to attract. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— Hoofdstad Brasserie Nieuwe Doelenstraat 2-14 020-5311619, reservations advised www.hoofdstadbrasserie.nl  Open: Mon-Sun 12.00-15.00 and 18.00-23.00 ——— #lunch #dinner #hoteldeleurope #amstel #amsterdamcentre #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

Indonesia was a former Dutch colony & has left its mark in the Netherlands with its cuisine. There are many Indonesian restaurants in Amsterdam & we decided to try one just to see how authentic the food is. MAX was recommended by our hotel & we tried the Rijsttafel (Indonesian banquet). Many small Indonesian dishes are served together with rice for sharing. I'd say the dishes are somewhat authentic, though adapted to suit the locals' taste. For example, the curry dishes weren't spicy at all (at least not to the Indonesian standard) & the achar had cauliflowers & capsicum. #Rijsttafel #indonesianfood #foodinmymouth #foodphotography #ilovesharingfood #foodporn #foodforfoodies #foodspotting #fooddiary #sharefood #food #instafood #foodgasm #burpple #amsterdamfood #travel #travelphotography #wanderlust #traveling #travelgram #holiday #vacation #instatravel #amsterdam

One of the most famous Grand Cafes in Amsterdam. I stumbled upon this place on our hunt for good food. The cozy interior with the beautiful art decor details made it feel like I just walked out of Dutch beauty right into modern Parisian romance. The salad beef carpaccio was definitely one of the best I've ever had served with a blend of pine nuts, Parmesan and pesto, and for someone who is always on the hunt for a good carpaccio, this definitely exceeded my expectations. With truffle in abundance, I couldn't resist a meal here! Definitely a tick on the list for all the things my tummy loves!  For those who DM'd me about my previous food post about price points, this was comparatively  affordable taking into consideration the quality of service, food & ambience.  #theragtradeeats #theragtradetravels . . . . . . . #foodie #food #foodgasm #eatingfortheinsta #foodbloggers #lifestyle #travel #amsterdamfood #truffle #foodporn #travelblogger

The Duchess is located opposite of the W Hotel and housed in the old KAS Bank Building it is beautifully done! Service is a little American, with the 'Hi, my name is Peter and I am your host for tonight', but it is prompt, friendly and spot on!  The food not only tickles your tastebuds, several dishes have some form of spectacular table preparation. If you are a chocolate fan: try the chocolate explosion. And if you don't want to be wheeled out at the end of your dinner: share it! We think The Duchess is gonna be a beloved, young acting, golden oldie in Amsterdam. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #restaurant #lunch #dinner #theduchess #kasbank #whotels #spuistraat #amsterdam #bresaola #fennelseed  #amsterdam  #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

Restaurant Moon in A'dam Toren is open. And we like it. The revolving restaurants makes one round every hour and makes you ooooh and aaaah for the stunning views of Amsterdam. So if you have company that you hate, just take a seat and look outside. But we suggest to go with people you adore, because not only the views are great, the food is too. Jaimie and his team create beautiful and tasteful dishes served in a set 5 or 8 course dinner. They co-create it with a line up of renowned Dutch music artists of which Thomas Acda is the first. Service had some startup problems where after the main course we had seen the 10th waiter at our table. Felt like the service sections didn't move along with the tables. But hey, it's only their second week. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #revolvingrestaurant #dinner #lunch #setmenu #lookout #Moon #RestaurantMoon.nl #AdamToren #AdamToren.nl #IJoever #amsterdamnoord #amsterdam #wine #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram  #adamtoren #adamlookout  #scallops #radish #greenapple #theartofplating #foodporn

Vondelpark/3's biggest feature is definitely its large sunny terrace overlooking the park. It has recently celebrated its first year anniversary and is here to stay. Service is a mix of hospitality minded people and students running drinks and dishes. The food is good in taste and presentation. The fresh tuna on the Niçoise salad was served medium rare. Perfect! However we like our egg on the Caesar poached, and think that the choice for a cooked one is merely based on the number of dishes that need to be prepared then on the connoisseurs' taste. They do a very nice family breakfast where your table is loaded with tasty items. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #breakfast #lunch # dinner #drinks #terrace #restaurant #vondelpark/3 #vondelpark3.nl #vondelpark #filmmuseum #vondelcs #vanbaerle  #vondelkerk #amsterdamzuid #ceasar #nicoise #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

We revisited our friends of RIJKS last week because we had something to celebrate. We were almost as satisfied as last time. The food was amazing! Surprising and inspiring dishes that combine the best of food heaven: mouth-watering taste, all different textures creating sensational mouthfeel, cooked to perfection and served in extraordinary ways. This time we sat on the terrace facing the Rijksmuseum in soft yellow raking light. Just like the illumination used by the famous 'Hollandse Meesters' inside. Now partly the weather was at the base of our less experience in service. It was terrace weather at 5, they had to move everything inside at 6 because of expected rain and started to set the tabes outside again at 7, what made service become a little chaotic. Also some of the service staff seemed a little out of tone in terms of behavior and clothing. One couldn’t stand still and explained the impressive dishes like he was on some sort of narcotic, while another was afraid to make eye contact and therefore stared at his unpolished shoes. Not something to expect when you enjoy an evening at this beautiful restaurant. The sommelier however did a great job, smile on his face, great wine/food pairing and not afraid to react to a joke. Because RIJKS is still on our Amsterdam Favorites list, we hope they take some time to not only polish the shoes. The kitchen deserves it! If you want to visit the RIJKS at a special occasion: on the 21st of august from 11pm on the doors stay open until 3am and they serve nothing but chicken and magnums of wine. You can reserve on their website. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— RIJKS Museumplein 2 020-6747555, reservations required www.rijksrestaurant.nl Open: Mon-Sat 11.30-23.00, Sun 11.30-21.00 ——— #lunch #dinner #rijksmuseum #museumplein #amsterdamcentre #amsterdamoudzuid #amsterdamzuid #amsterdamoldsouth #amsterdamsouth #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

This one is Turkish food from the central part of Turkey originated in Konya and one of my favourite. Etli Ekmek or "bread with meat" has very thinner and crispy base and topping is not spicy mostly based on thinly chopped green pepper,tomato and minced meat. My favourite is "kusbasili" which means thinly chopped lamb fillet instead of minced meat. Havzan is a small,clean restaurant offering very friendly service. Soups are also nice. Just give it a try! #amsterdam #pastaconsardeamsterdam #amsterdamfood

Amsterdam appears to be the capital of street food and we are taking full advantage! There's even amazing Vegetarian food to be had all over the place and a perfect example is this Vegetarian Hot Dog. A superb herb sausage with all the essential toppings. It even makes the meaty hot dog (that was actually delicious) look nowhere near as interesting. Take that.  Dear Sydney, our Vego is never coming back. Apologies, TGOF  In all seriousness though, this city has truly amazing food that offers something for everyone. Definitely add it to your to-do list if you are looking for more than the seedy "cafes" found in the overpriced Red Light District. #TGOFeatoutEurope

Aight, so there's this dude who owns a small Japanese restaurant on the top floor of an Asian grocery. It's a one man show. He takes your order and you can see him cook and prepare food right there in front of you. He moves frantically when there are be several people waiting (and that's often the case), but don't worry about the wait for your ramen or pancakes. Take a seat. He will serve you your dish. I went on a Sunday and wanted to go again the next day to try another dish. However, he doesn't work on Mondays and Tuesdays. I was saddened by this fact so I decided that I wanted to tip him because the ramen was delishhh. But he humbly wouldn't accept my tip. Sir, you are an awesome chef. The place is kind of a secret but I'm sure more and more people will find it and it won't be such a secret anymore. Also, his restaurant is only open, at the most, 5 hours each day. I hope to come visit you again and try those pancakes.  #takajapanesekitchen #Amsterdam #amsterdamfood #netherlands #ramen #japanesecuisine #food #foodie #foodporn #yum

Vergulden Eenhoorn Amsterdam •  In hindsight it would have been better to take a picture of the beautiful garden filled with beach chairs instead of the dark interior of the farm. Anyway, De Vergulden Eenhoorn is a farm in the midst of Amsterdam. A cozy place, where a fireplace is lit and the atmosphere is calm and serene. The business cards represent the colorful plates of the kitchen and the natural ingredients. Back to the roots of 1792, when city life was a little more peaceful as it is now. I did not managed to found the gilding unicorn yet.🦄 I'll be back.  ___________________ #amsterdam #seemyamsterdam #seemycity #citygarden #cityfarm #hiddengem #verguldeneenhoorn #gramthedam #amsterdamfood #waaramsterdameet #amsterdamfoodie #cityexplorer #whatdoesthebusinesscardsay #brandidentity #branding #branding #importanceofgraphicdesign #graphicdesign

Herengracht is an old favorite with a terrace out front and not so well known garden in the back. The sun doesn't have to come out to sit comfortably, because the heaters do their work. Service is friendly and adequate and the menu is extensive and offers quality food and drinks. We ordered steak tartare on farmers bread and a small salad on the side. Tasty! There used to be this restaurant on Westerstraat called Fraiche, but then they moved over to Cut Throat and a place called Gin Neo moved in where Fraiche was but then everyone blinked and the Gin Neo people swapped out the Westerstraat location with their other restaurant The Fish Toko and moved Gin Neo to a place on Noorderstraat where Frya used to be. Make sense? Anyway, there's a place called The Fish Toko on Westerstraat and it's pretty good. They have fish tacos every day and seafood ramen (!!) on Sundays. Amsterdam playgrounds have admirably taken the whole idea of “safety” out of the picture. Whereas in most cities there’s idiot-proof jungle gyms and squishy mats on the ground, Amsterdam’s playground designers never stopped to say “What if…” on their quest for “How big can we go?” (Have you seen the new playground on Frederik Hendrik Plantsoen?! Insane.) TIP – In the long summer days, the children eventually have to go in, eat dinner, and do whatever else children do. Which means…the playgrounds are empty! Prime time to get after some slides or this zipline thing in Bos en Lommer.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. We finally made it to the girls and guys of Pluk, a fine addition to the healthy lunchrooms in Amsterdam. They have done a great job interior wise and sell loads of bring home items.  When you enter, the male to female ratio drops dramatically. But that's nothing to worry about. What you do need to worry about is the danger of ordering the entire menu. The freshly prepared food and drinks are great here! They tickle your tastebuds and pleasure the eyes.  Service wise: we love table service, but the plukkers chose differently. Fair. All in all we are more then ok with that. Our favourite street snack in Amsterdam. The herring fish bread. Fish-dog. Gonna try to make one myself 🐠🐟🍞 #herring #fishbread #fishroll  #streetsnack #amsterdamfood

#TBT to this herring fish 🐟, a well-know street food in Amsterdam 🇳🇱. Herring is essentially raw fish eaten with onions and pickles 😋, and you can get it for 3 euros ($4 CAD). It is an acquired taste! If I have to describe, the texture is soft and it has a nice bite to it. The fish taste and smell fresh & salty 🐟! There are a few spots in Amsterdam where you can get herring fish ☺. Stubbe's Haring is next to Amsterdam Central Station and it is perhaps the most convenient spot. If not, visit Vishuisje Herengracht and enjoy a nice walk around the canals 😘. -- #HangryFoodies #fbcigers #herring #eatingeurope #amsterdamfood #amsfood #delicious #foodie #lovefood #getinmybelly #fujifilm #foodpics #🐟#netherlands #forkyeah #Tastingtable #myfujifilm #feedmyphone #eatfamous #fujifeed #fujifilmX_US #passionpassport #ATxNL16 #travelblogger #🇳🇱

Как назло, только форель, лосось и иже с ними. Все официанты пожимали плечами при нашем "ну,Селдь" (я,конечно,помнила, что на букву "Х" , но слово вылетело из головы!) Herring ,чтоб ее. Это как в России все иностранцы ждут медведей с балалайкой на улице. Короче, в супермаркете купили этот голландский деликатес. Пальчики оближешь,ммм💋

Hollands superfood! Aardappelen zijn een bron van vezels en vitamine B6. Ze zijn een goede bron van energie voor je lichaam en helpen voor een goede darmwerking.  Vitamine B6 voor je spieren  Deze vitamine is niet alleen belangrijk voor de (energie)stofwisseling, maar levert ook een bijdrage aan de energievoorziening in de spieren.  Net als het gehele lichaam brandstof nodig heeft in de vorm van energie, hebben de spieren dit ook nodig. Dit is natuurlijk ook van belang tijdens het sporten. Thanks to @voedingsweetjes volg ze voor leuke en handige weetjes over al je voeding!

30 min wait in line for Best Thai in town. 👌  THAI BIRD RESTAURANT  An elegant restaurant with more than 100 seats, Thai Bird serves tasty dishes to a crowd of hungry diners nightly. Although the restaurant is large, there seems to be a line out the door most evenings. The wait is never very long however, and soon you will be seated with a Singha in hand (did you know it is pronounced “Sing” and not “Sing-ha”?). Begin your meal by sharing an order of loempia or saté, tom yum soup, or perhaps Northern Thai lobster meatballs. The menu has something for everyone, with seafood, chicken, noodle, beef and vegetarian dishes. Most main courses run from €15-18 each and come with steamed rice. Service is quick and friendly.  #amsterdamfood #amsterdam #thai #redcurry #instafood #delicious

Our stroll on the Amsterdam Marine Land of the Dutch Navy lead us to the Scheepskameel. Well, to be honest, it was the other way round, because the rumors about this place were very positive. Entering the Scheepskameel you immediately recognize the style of its older sister Rijsel. Both restaurants are housed in historic buildings, the interior tuned to it. This building used to be an education center for Naval chefs. In a new restaurant you would expect a lot of training and learning going on, but the open kitchen seems to be an oasis of tranquillity and harmony. The menu hosts numerous small dishes with a focus on raw ingredients and not too much focus on minimalistic presentations. It is all about the taste and we think it's delicious! In the wine department the Scheepskameel has made the choice to only serve German wines. Daring, but surprisingly well done! The service is of the kind that we would like to see more in Amsterdam. Friendly, courteous, expert.  All in all: this is another go people! Reservations are required, because they have had fully booked services from the start on. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— Scheepskameel Kattenburgerstraat 7, building 024 020-3379680, reservations advised!  www.scheepskameel.nl Open: Tue-Sat 18.00-end ——————————————————————— #dinner #scheepskameel #marineterrein #marine #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview ——————————————————————— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites. Café Restaurant Hoogendam has a great terrace facing the sun for a very long long time and it is heated during te winter. They haven’t been able to overcome the mediocre start they had (the chef leaving premature, the exposure of the fact that the organic chicken on the menu isn’t organic at all and the ambiance feeling more like an empty ballroom, then a cosy Amsterdam hangout). We went back an tried it several times more over the past weeks, but still have the mediocre word in our head. Mimi Latteria Milanese is located on the long long Kerkstraat near the corner with the Nieuwe Spiegelstraat. It is inspired on the small grocery stores that popped up in the post-war 50’s in Milan selling farmers products and serving home cooked dishes. This inspiration is to be found in the menu solely, because in the ambiance you would expect an ‘artisan’ touch but it is very contemporary. The restaurant is Italian owned and staffed, something we appreciate and gives a little confidence in taste. The menu provides a cross-section of Italian cuisine. Bruschette, some soups, pastas, and classic mains like vitello tonnato, coteletta alla Milanese, some salads and last but not least dolce like Tiramisù and dark chocolate pie. We chose for the Millefoglie, made of bread, vegetable and tomato caponata and mozzarella. Now technically what was on our plate was mozzarella, but after smoking it for about 15 minutes, the taste becomes much more dominant and then it is called scamorza. Not something we particularly appreciate and where other dishes were on the menu with scamorza specifically named, this dish hadn’t. So we asked for some mozzarella instead and were told that this was actually mozzarella, but then smoked. After a short discussion about clear communication and some waiting for the new dish, we got what we wanted. And it was more then tasty the way it was advertised. We also tried and liked some Italian sweets and coffee. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— MIMI Latteria Milanese Kerkstraat 148 020-7370239, reservations possible www.facebook.com/latteriamilanese/ Open: Mon-Sun 8.00-22.00 ——— #breakfast #coffee #lunch #dinner #kerkstraat #museumplein #amsterdamcentre #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

The Westerpark hosts several great places to go to for lunch, drinks or an easy dinner. Pacific Parc has gotten some severe nearby competition over the last years (e.g. Mossel & Gin, Brouwerij Troost, Wester Wijnfabriek). These places are run by young, enthusiastic, hospitality minded people. In our multiple visits, we unfortunately didn't get this vibe at Pacific Parc. But hey: the biggest pro is the terrace and the food is ok! The large salads we had were sufficient in size, tasty and fresh. Only the Pata Negra mentioned on the menu was replaced by the cheaper Jamón Serrano.  Do we still come here? Uhm yes. Because the sunny terrace is great and it is a great place if you don't want to cook yourself one night. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— Pacific Parc Polonceaukade 23 020-4887778, reservations possible www.pacificparc.nl Open: Mon-Sun 11.00-end ——————————————————————— #dinner #pacificparc #westerpark #mosselengin #westerwijnfabriek #brouwerijtroost #polonceaukade #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #patanegra #jamonserrano #asparagus ——————————————————————— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites. Have you guys tried Mojo? It's a delicious Cuban marinade made with lashings of sour orange juice, plenty of cumin, garlic and oregano. If you don't have access to sour oranges, then no problem, use normal fresh orange's and lime juice, to achieve that tart taste. There are many variations of the recipe as there are with many recipes. You can use it on seafood, meats, it's usually used a lot with pork or chicken. Here I've used it on red snapper. If you like garlic and the tart flavours, this one is for you. Recipe on the website soon, go to www.nyamfoodie.com  By the way I'm hosting a pop up at Scrapyard Cafe on Wednesday 8th March. If the pictures on this feed make your mouth water, why don't you come and try some of my food for yourself. Mashua in Amsterdam is by far the most romantic restaurant I've ever been to, with some of the best Peruvian food I've had in my life (and I've had a lot, growing up going to Peru every summer for two months since I was 6.) The ingredients were of the highest quality, assembled in the traditional Peruvian manner with attention to detail. You could taste the love in each dish! The ambiance was intimate and sensual, with black chandeliers throughout and deep red tones adorning the interior of the restaurant. My view was of a beautiful canal on a truly picturesque Amsterdam side street. Hands down one of the best travel experiences I've had. ❤

... rincontrare Sander van Melick, e riuscire a sollecitare un suo sorriso... come lui fa sorridere noi con i suoi piatti... attraversi il canale, il freddo ed il gelo ti segna mani e faccia, i metri sono pochi da fare. Arrivi al cafe modern e lo trovi preso, indaffarato, concentrato. Il menu é quello di giornata... la mis en bouche... una ricottina cotta al forno accompagnata da una barbabietola rossa, l'olio li tiene insieme... altri piatti arrivano che divori... il pezzo forte le animelle... alimenti antichi... alimenti che ti fanno ricordare che anche le interiora... sono prelibatezza... il servizio finisce... e Sander finalmente alza la testa. Vede i suoi ospiti... si ricorda di me della mia ultima visita... che arrivo da lontano. Mi sorride. Gli faccio capire che penso alla sua cucina come a quella di casa... non mi sento un cliente ma un amico invitato... Sander sul partire ci sorride e ci prepara per il rientro a casa... fuori imperversano -5 gradi ed un distillato di pera williams ci aiuterà nel cammino di rientro a casa. Alla prossima caro amico... #cafemodern_amsterdam  #cafemoderamsterdam #sandervanmelick #amsterdamnoord #amsterdamfood #iamsterdam #amsterdam #amsterdamcity #amsterdam🇳🇱 #amsterdamcanals #amsterdamlove #mangiarecomeunavolta #unnapoletanoaparigi #amsterdamfoodguide

Bistro Zuidlande is tucked away at the end of the spaarndammerbuurt and part of its charm is that they cook good meals, but are very unpretentious. The menu is small, but there is always a choice of daily specials. The chef Arend Nieboer has cooked at famous Michelin star restaurants and does his shopping daily and seasonal. Madam is the panorama bar and restaurant on the 20th floor of the newly developed @adam_toren. It is the square part, just beneath the observation desk (HELLO IM ADAM) and above the 19th floor revolving restaurant where they will serve 5- and 8-course dinners. Madam has a more brasserie style menu with classics like steak tartar, Caesar salad and rack of lamb.  Going up in a spectacular elevator and welcomed with a glass of Champagne, we were first overtaken by the VIEW! Words can't describe it properly, but maybe you can stay tuned on @amsterdamview and see for yourself.  Our sneak peak 4 course dinner started with smoked salmon followed by tom kha kai, supreme chicken and yes: there was still some room for a chocolate mousse. We loved it. Service and food are only in need of some fine tuning, but all is done from the heart.  We are curious what Moon is going to be like! But Madam had a terrific first try out evening! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #restaurant #club #cocktails #lookout #brasserie #Madam #MadamAmsterdam.nl #AdamToren #AdamToren.nl #IJoever #amsterdamnoord #amsterdam #wine #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram  #adamtoren #adamlookout #preopening #sneakpeak #tryoutdinner

Blank canvas... Meringue is always so pretty when it's perfectly white and fluffly! I prefer italian meringue over french meringue for my lemon pies, because I "cook" the eggwhites when incorporating the boiling hot sugar syrup making it more sticky and gooey than the lighter french version. Also italian meringue stays intact for much longer, whereas french meringue becomes runny again quite quickly and doesn't stay good for long. This blank canvas is just dying to get caressed by the flames of a blowtorch and turn into caramelised brown meringue!!!
Meringue heaven!!!

Proudly presenting this week's #ff #featuredfermenter @malicafe_organic_vegan_food  #amsterdamfood  Malicafe offers a delicious array of #Macrobiotic inspired vegan food, composed with locally and house grown vegetables and fruits, cooked together with traditional Japanese ingredients. Whole food, harmony with world, better environment, your smile - that's what we want. Apart from the catering service and popup events, they run various cooking programs and one day workshops.  Stop by, have a bite, say hello, follow a workshop, why not then this miso & #donabe cooking and lunch workshop next Saturday 10 December?  https://www.facebook.com/events/718048655015175/?ti=icl  Psssst- they do #kombucha workshops sometimes as well!

Because the old V&D building doesn't have a new tenant yet, the owner invited BAUT to reside in it. And they are happily doing so since two weeks under the original name of BAUT & Dreesmann. When you have visited BAUT in one of its previous locations (Wibautstraat, Stadionplein or Prinses Irenestraat) you know what you can expect. A raw interior, some street art and quality food and service. The place is really special. Where V&D had blinded every single window to put non selling products against, B&D has opened them up offering great views over the Rokin. The restaurant and bar are in two separate areas. The bar is open since yesterday evening, offering live DJ's. The food we had in the restaurant was good. The service we would say has some start up problems.  The moving circus is on this location until January. We are curious where they go afterwards! ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— BAUT & Dreesmann Rokin 146 020-4659260, reservations advised www.bautamsterdam.nl  Open: Sun-Thu 10.00-1.00, Sat-Sun 10.00-0300 Bar open only on Thu-Sat ——— #lunch #dinner #drinks #streetart #dj #rokin #vroomendreesmann #v&d #baut #bautendreesmann #b&d #amsterdamcentre #amsterdamcenter #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

De Pijp, an Amsterdam neighborhood found just south of the canal ring, translates into English as 'The Pipe’ - an early reference to either the public prostitution or the shape of the neighborhood. Historians disagree.  For the last couple of years, an actual pipe, the Amsterdam metro, has been digging its way under De Pijp. Not surprisingly, building a subway in a city that's below sea level is kind of tricky and led to the misfortune which was the 'Great Heineken Debacle of 2014,' when the Heineken brewery fell into a giant sinkhole. Even without its top tourist destination and the constant fear of sudden, gaping pits, De Pijp has managed to evolve into a neighborhood that lifestyle bloggers describe as “trendy” and “alive.” On sunny afternoons, try Sarphatipark if you're inclined to pop the top and get some color. The Albert Cuyp Market (#albertcuypmarkt) is (supposedly) the “largest daytime market in Europe” and has a few interesting food stands, but you're better off heading to Pho 91 (@pho91amsterdam), Spaghetteria (@spaghetteria_pastabar), or The Butcher (@thebutcheramsterdam). (**TIP - There’s also great Surinamese just off the market on Eerste van der Helststraat.) For shopping, there’s Charlie + Mary (@charlieplusmary), All The Luck In The World… (@alltheluckintheworld), and several other boutiques on the same block of Gerard Doustraat. If you're working away from the office, Stadskantine has plenty of window seating and a good atmosphere. For coffee, Scandinavian Embassy (@scandinavianembassy) and CT Coffee & Coconuts (@coffeecoconuts) are good spots.  Find more suggestions for the best of De Pijp on Sightseen's Neighbourhood Collections.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. 📸👉@lexflex81  Oh, yeah…they opened a Cannibale Royale in the Red Light District. Around the corner from Sichuan Kitchen (one of Sightseen’s favorites) and light-years from the @cannibaleroyale locations in Spui and De Pijp. The RLD version stands oddly on a street of terrible tourist pizza and waffles for stoned hostelists. But maybe when you can't get a table at the Spui location (and you're feeling particularly patient), it's worth firing up the bike bell and navigating the zombie hordes for some ribs in the RLD. Gone Skiing! 🎿🏔⛷🏂 Last night we were trying to order some takeout. Saturday night and all the restaurants in the neighborhood were closed! Our friends said it was because of "ski week". Huh??? Apparently this is the week in Amsterdam when all the kids are out from school, so they can take ski vacations with their families. I find that so refreshing. And thoughtful. And putting priorities in the right place. When people ask why we moved to Europe, we always say that we wanted to live the "European Lifestyle". This is the sort of thing we're referring to.  I'm not sure it would go over so well in the U.S., where I'm from.  How do you feel about it? Would you be mad if you couldn't order takeout on Saturday because everyone went skiing? Haha. I love it!
Refreshing & beautiful, just like a Friday night #carteramsterdam

Ter Marsch & Co just popped up in the hopefully soon to be renovated NH Jolly Carlton Hotel. The Rotterdam concept specializes in award winning burgers. We had two of those out of a menu of 6. Last night's dinner of Indonesian rijsttafel (rice table). It's several small portions of dishes like chicken sate, beef rendang, green beans in coconut milk etc.

Rijsttafel - The must try if you're in Amsterdam.  Rijsttafel translated means rice table where the food is served tapas style, giving you the chance to try a little bit of everything.  Loved the food. If you find yourself in Amsterdam, this take on Indonesian food is a must 🍚  #jetsetnomeats #localeats #localfood #eatlikealocal #eatingamsterdam #amsterdamfood #rijsttafel  #indonesianfood

#Rijsttafel is adopted from #Dutch during the colonial era in Indonesia. The words simply means "rice table". The plan was to go Salsa Shop. People had been raving about it for some time. One look at the food though and Mr.G and I were both standing outside with a sad face. Through the pouring rain we ran all the way to Wagamama. To spice things up, and feel like I was trying out something new anyhow, I was brave and decided to try out a new dish. Usually, I go for Yasai Itame or Chicken Kare Lomen, but this time I took Chicken Raisukaree–and wasn't disappointed at all. Wagamama delivers, baby! What you see on the plate is chicken stir-fried in a coconut and lime curry sauce with mangetout, peppers, red and spring onions served on sticky white rice and garnished with red chillies, coriander and lime. I am also in love with the space, and actually, I like this whole street nowadays. The restaurants are mainstream but they are all pretty pimped up. Great for a super easy dinner with friends before taking the party elsewhere. #dontbeasnob #spiceitup #ilike #chicken #raisukaree #asianfood #food #wagamama #amstelstraat #rembrandtplein #amsterdam #amsterdamdinner #amsterdameats #amsterdamfood

Everybody tries to crack the secret that makes me awesome, but here’s the honest truth: I just don't know. I am bit like superman. No clue what I’m made of or where I came from. Only thing I know is that I’m VEGAN. And I’m allergic to Kryptonite.  It makes me happy to know a Sir Hummus plate isn’t complete without me! 🤗

I went hunting in my boss' fridge during a late night shift yesterday. Found spinach, pumpkin, lentils, organic cherry tomatoes, salmon and eggs. And I created this finger licking good bowl of veggie awesomeness. Roasted the tomatoes - lentils and pumpkin in the oven with tamari, cumin, ras el hanout and cayenne. Scrambled the eggs with salmon and miso and layered it on top of some fresh spinach. And sprinkled some roasted pumpkinseeds on top. Kind of Moroccan -Japanese fusion thingy. Pretty good. It made me feel at home in an empty loft at 22pm. 🍅🍳🍆 At the moment I'm enjoying a little pre-Easter twosomeparty in rural Tuitjehorn with my Sol-mate 🌞 cooking spicy curries, drinking Syrah #vinnaturel and learning about the healing powers of herbs and other green leafy creatures. Hmm feels good to be out of Amsterdam. I literally have more space in my body and mind.

We were back at Restaurant MOON in A'dam Toren to show you the revolving restaurant. Below the review from our previous visit.  We give service an extra star this time! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Moon in A'dam Toren is open. And we like it. The revolving restaurants makes one round every hour and makes you ooooh and aaaah for the stunning views of Amsterdam. So if you have company that you hate, just take a seat and look outside. But we suggest to go with people you adore, because not only the views are great, the food is too. Jaimie and his team create beautiful and tasteful dishes served in a set 5 or 8 course dinner. They co-create it with a line up of renowned Dutch music artists of which Thomas Acda is the first. Service had some startup problems where after the main course we had seen the 10th waiter at our table. Felt like the service sections didn't move along with the tables. But hey, it's only their second week. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #revolvingrestaurant #dinner #lunch #setmenu #lookout #Moon #RestaurantMoon.nl #AdamToren #AdamToren.nl #IJoever #amsterdamnoord #amsterdam #wine #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram  #adamtoren #adamlookout  @neilengelen @jaimievanheije @sandergroet

Ordered: rib eye and lady Steak Ordered at @cafecarbon Amsterdam 🍴 Yes, a real flame grilled steak. That's what you get at Café Carbon. I was recommended this place by a few people, so naturally it didn't take me long to see and taste this for myself. We ordered twi different steaks, one rib eye and one lady steak, which is a tenderloin. They have others as well, you can go al out with a T-bone as well. I liked the steak, it was well prepared. Seasoned it with a bit more salt, it didn't need any more! While waiting I saw a few very good looking spareribs getting carried to other tables 😐. I'm not done here yet. Half of the Ohmykase team was in Amsterdam this past holiday weekend, and, of course, had to find at least one sushi meal while in the city. We settled on the Michelin-rated Yamazato, located at the Hotel Okura Amsterdam. We were immediately greeted by a friendly waitstaff and seated promptly at the sushi bar. The serenity of the hotel and restaurant itself almost made it feel as though we were transported back to Japan. In particular we liked how the sushi bar was virtually hidden from the main dining room to add a more intimate vibe between those dining at the bar and the two chefs. While we enjoyed the fish quality and the chef's preparation of nigiri, we did think that there was room for improvement with the taste and texture of the rice, as well as with certain ingredients which could use additional refinement to expand the flavors. We do acknowledge that it may be a bit unfair to compare this meal to ones we've had at both Michelin-rated and non Michelin-rated sushi counters in NYC (since the never ending competition in NYC can be a factor in having chefs constantly refine techniques), however,  Yamazato may be worth visiting if you're ever in the mood for a higher-end sushi meal in Amsterdam

Taste Amsterdam - Amstelpark, 2nd - 5th June.  Last year we spent a sun-soaked day here, eating & drinking until we ran out of the taste currency 'florijnen'. It was great & I've been looking forward to this years ever since.  This is a gathering of Amsterdam's top restaurants offering a number of dishes each. Also, there are bars of every description; cocktail, G&T, beer, champagne, the lot!  Also cooking demonstrations, workshops & plenty to occupy the kids. The highlight for them last year was a huge ferris wheel ride... for me it was the glass of champagne you got with each ride! 👍🏻 There is also a 'Taste of Kids' area, great for pre-schoolers & older.  My tip would be to get there early to grab somewhere nice to lounge & set up camp. Also take lots of money as the florijnen tend to go pretty quickly!  Cannot wait!  #tasteofamsterdam2016 #tasteofamsterdam #tastefestival #amsterdamfood #amsterdamfoodfestival #amsterdamforkids #kidsinamsterdam #kindvriendelijk #amsterdamrestaurants #iamsterdam #gramthedam #iloveamsterdam #igamsterdam #igersamsterdam #thingstodoinamsterdam #exploreamsterdam #instaamsterdam #imamsterdam #exploreamsterdam #mamasinamsterdam #amstergram #wonderlustamsterdam

Saravanaa Bhavan is the new positive surprise in Indian vegetarian delight. Imagine a purple lid ceiling, the ugliest chesterfield chairs available and staff that doesn't know exactly what it serves. But hey, they are friendly. But then add the extensive menu with loads and loads of deliciously prepared dishes and the 75% Indian people that are visiting this restaurant. And when they are here in these big numbers, you know it is good. And they are helpful! Because you next table neighbors know what you should order. Because we couldn't choose, we ordered the Saravanaa Special with all kind of small tries, white rice and papadum. And it was great! Reservations are advised.  This is a go people! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️ ——————————————————————— #indianfood #restaurant #saravanaabhavan #saravanaabhavan.nl #stadhouderskade #vanwoustraat #depijp #amsterdam #dosa #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

You know those little, white paddleboats in the canals? How many relationships have they ended? How many honeymooners came to Amsterdam and left on separate flights after the paddleboats? Has anyone over the age of 13 had fun on a paddleboat ever?  We understand — they’re there, it’s summer in Amsterdam, you’re thinking: ‘What if we get one of those paddleboats? That would be fun!’ But after 10 minutes of paddling around you realize it isn’t fun. In fact, it’s terrible — people on the bridges throw trash on you, the big tourist boats (themselves an influencer in the Amsterdam divorce rate) try to run you over, and the pedaling. Unless you’re a pregnant person at the gym, pedalling in a reclined position isn’t natural. Human beings aren’t made to sit back and pedal. Slouch in front of a glowing screen for 12 hours at a time? No problem. Type with our thumbs? Fine. But seated pedaling? That’s just crazy talk.  Skip the paddleboats. Download Sightseen for free on the App Store (*link in bio*) to quickly find all the best to eat, drink, see, and do in Amsterdam. Do it for your marriage.  We added a Collection of events, openings, and things to do in August to Sightseen. You can find it on the homepage in the app or as a post on the Sightseen Medium account. Check it out and message us if we missed anything.  #sightseenapp  #Amsterdam #iamsterdam #igersamsterdam #amsterdamcity #amsterdamlife #amstergram #gramthedam #amsterdamworld #thankyouamsterdam #instaamsterdam #bestofamsterdam #visitamsterdam #amsterdamshots #amsterdambound #amsterdamstyle #amsterdamfood #eurotravel #amsterdamfoodie #amsterdamhotspot #canaltourists #amsterdamworld

Worst Winecafé is a little tucked away in the Barentszstraat near the Haarlemmersquare. They serve fine small dishes for yourself or to share. Their great wine selection is served with passion and know-how. We love it, but it is rare in Amsterdam... We started of with some bread (baked daily at Restaurant As), anchovies with broad beans and pecorino and a clean green salad with mustard dressing. A good start! Tasty and pure.  From the sausage (worst) department we ordered fennel sausage served with braised pepper and fennel and the chicken sausage which came with morels and creamy spinach. We loved the former, liked the latter.  The cosy atmosphere and relaxed setting is perfect for a after work evening or laid back weekend night. Bike into the Zeeheldenbuurt and check it out! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— Worst Wijncafé Barentszstraat 171 020-6256167 www.deworst.nl Open: Tue-Sat 12.00-0.00, Sun 10.00-22.00 ——————————————————————— #restaurant #dinner #lunch #wine #winecafé #Worst #zeeheldenbuurt #haarlemmerplein #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #sausage #fennel ——————————————————————— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.

Dream come true. A visit to the oldest Jewish pickle shop in Amsterdam. Five generations have had this shop. Crispy and perfect. Have a little bag with me to bring back to Sweden. Reports about this pickle shop exclaim that Van Gogh wrote in his diaries about the yellow of these pickles and there have been studies to compare the yellows in his Sunflower paintings with De Leeuw's yellow pickes. They are apparently a match! #pickla #pickles #foodhunter #vangoghspickles #vangogh #foodfromheaven #amsterdamfood #foodforthought #foodforfoodies
